Working with the existing team to formulate ideas on how to improve standard product by actively gathering and understanding customer and stakeholder needs. Presenting ideas to Team Manager and Senior Leadership that will improve usability and enhance user interface designs including navigation, ensuring alignment with the vision and product strategy roadmap.

Role specific accountabilities

Creating Wireframes, UI Designs, mock-ups as required for development

Create / Maintain overall UI Templating / Style for our products

Reviewing existing systems for UX/Design Improvements

Work with developers to help execute product styling

Able to research adequately to support design decisions

Qualifications

A sound general level of academic education, a minimum of English and Mathematics GCSE grade... C;

Skills

Good, accurate keyboard skills and ICT competence;

Analytical and problem solving skills;

Excellent attention to detail;

Able to work as an effective team member;

Ability to work under pressure;

Good organisation skills;

Excellent communication skills;

Experience - Required

At least 1 year experience in a UX Design role.

Portfolio of recent work

Experience in implementing accessibility standards

